A 7-year-old boy has reportedly died in an accident as a commercial motorcycle had a head-on collision with a vehicle. He died on the spot. The incident occurred in the New year’s eve at Oveiwn Community, in Udu Local Government Area of Delta State. The deceased’s mother, Jennifer Timothy broke her legs. Her daughter sustained serious injuries on the chin and other body parts, DAILY POST reports. It was learnt that the incident occurred when the mother of the two children moving on a commercial motorcycle from Orhunwhorhun to Ovwian to observe the crossover service. The injured victims, Jennifer Timothy and her daughter were rushed to the Central Hospital, Warri, for medical treatment.